Ekiti State Agriculture Commissioner, Prince Olabode Adetoyi, has disclosed the state government’s plan to produce over one million metric tonnes of rice yearly. Olabode, who lamented the country’s unquantifiable loss from importation of rice, said, “Ekiti Rice Pyramid Project’ is part of attempts to discourage importation of rice and boost local production of highly nutritious rice.” The commissioner, who spoke in Ado Ekiti on Saturday at a press conference heralding the official launch of Ekiti Rice Pyramid Project and inauguration of the 2021 wet season rice cultivation on Tuesday, said the state was already embarking on massive production of rice to be able to meet both local and external demands. He said, “The state government has brought in investors who are ready to invest in planting and processing of rice. The rice produced in the state would be standard and stone free.” He assured rice farmers and investors of adequate Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com